{
  "text": "The OSATS (Figure 1 ) has been extensively validated and shown to be an effective method for assessment of surgical skills [CITATION_1] . It does, however, require significant resources and time on the part of faculty evaluators [CITATION_2] . Over the past 15 years, it has moved from use in the laboratory setting to use in the operating theatre [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . OSATS is validated and used for the evaluation of both open and laparoscopic surgical skills. It is viewed as the standard for skills assessment [CITATION_6] .",
